Review of the Uralic peoples, languages and cultures, their modern situation; the various directions and stages in studying of Finno-Ugric languages. Formation and main characteristics of Estonian language; review of the description, research and development of the literary language since the 17th century up to now; review of the major research directions.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course gives an overview of Finno-Ugric Languages and Estonian Language, history of their studying and the main characteristics of this problematics. This review forms a basis for other linguistic courses.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student receives knowledge about the Uralic language family and of language groups relating to it, history of their studying, the main problems, the studying directions, the main researchers; about the principal features and formation of Estonian language, history of studying of Estonian language, the main problems, the approaches, the main researchers.
